snippet.textDisplay:
Well what they needed was proactive critical infrastructure preparedness!

There is a society that takes a proactive role in times of disaster; we are used to making fun of that society it is called Cuba.

The New York Times on the 10th of September 2017 wrote the following story

While the Cuban response to the storm seemed to be a well-oiled
machine elsewhere in the Caribbean the government reaction has been halting

This is the New York Times language for saying the Cubans have a well-oiled system of preventing and protecting people as they are not driven by private profit the way we are.

There is a lesson here but of course like all lessons if you're not open to learning the lesson well then you won't !
